# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1899-baltimore-orioles-season
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1899-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] The 19th century's version of the **Baltimore Orioles** were founded in 1882 as part of the new American Association.
[src:1899-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] Owned by wealthy Harry Von der Horst, the Orioles finished the season in last place with only 19 wins.
[src:1899-baltimore-orioles-season/1899-baltimore-orioles-season] The **1899 Baltimore Orioles season** was a season in American baseball.
[src:1899-baltimore-orioles-season/1899-baltimore-orioles-season] It was the Orioles' 18th season in the major leagues, their 8th in the National League, and their last overall.
[src:1899-baltimore-orioles-season/1899-baltimore-orioles-season] After the 1898 season, Orioles owner Harry Von der Horst acquired a controlling interest in the Brooklyn Bridegrooms ballclub and moved most of his star players and manager Ned Hanlon over to the Brooklyn team.
[src:1899-baltimore-orioles-season/1899-baltimore-orioles-season] The remaining team played the season under first year manager John McGraw and still won 86 games and finished in fourth place.
[src:1899-baltimore-orioles-season/1899-baltimore-orioles-season] After the season, the National League contracted and the Baltimore franchise was folded.
[src:1899-baltimore-orioles-season/1899-baltimore-orioles-season] The remaining players either were absorbed into Brooklyn or released to sign with another club.
